item.title: About Me
item.description: I graduated from Stanford with a B.S. in Computer Science in 2016, and have worked as a software engineer at the financial technology startup Addepar ever since. Starting Fall 2020, I’ll be at Princeton pursuing a Master’s in Computer Science. My interests run a wide gamut, encompassing the development of safe and fair artificial intelligence, the analysis and design of algorithms, and the application of each to public health and environmental management.
